The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA) using deep learning systems, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a self-critical training objective to improve the generalization of VQA models, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the VQA-CP dataset, which involves analyzing textual explanations, a task that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
